# WatchIO API layer

## Single abstraction

All backends implement `WatchIoClient` in `watchIoClient.ts`. Factory: `createWatchIoClient()` in `watchIoClientFactory.ts`.

```typescript
// Adding a transport requires all of:
// 1. New class implementing WatchIoClient
// 2. Factory switch case
// 3. ConnectionTransport in api/types.ts + constants/transport.ts
// 4. Proxy entries in vite.config.ts (if HTTP)
```

## Four transports (do not mix URL rules)

| Transport | Client | Base path | Tree naming |
|-----------|--------|-----------|-------------|
| `smcServer` | `SmcServerClient` | `/SmcServer1`, `/SmcServer2` | Slash paths (`Control/...`) |
| `sharedMemory` | `SharedMemoryWatchIoClient` | COM `WatchIoCom.ocx` | Dot paths |
| `watchIoHttp` | `HttpWatchIoClient` | `/watchio` | Dot paths (`C.Filter...`) |
| `watchIoWs` | `StompWatchIoClient` | STOMP dest `/watchio` | Dot paths |

SmcServer uses `parseSmcJson.ts`; WatchIO messages use `parseWatchIoMessage.ts` shape (`WatchIoMessage`).

## HTTP base URL

- Dev: `config.httpUrl === ''` → same-origin requests hit Vite proxy → `:8082`.
- Never hardcode `http://localhost:8082` in client code for dev; CORS breaks on `:5173`.

## Discovery

- `smcHttp.ts` — `GET /request` service list → `DiscoveredService[]`.
- SmcServer and WatchIO are separate registrations; `serverPath` comes from discovery, not guessed.

## Client responsibilities

- `fetchVarTree` / `fetchVarLeaves` — populate tree.
- `addVariable` / `removeVariable` / `setMonitorList` — polling or push subscription.
- `setVariable` — write parameter value.
- Emit normalized `WatchIoMessage` via `onMessage`; connection state via `onStatus`.

